===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm|en}} {{term|wid|lang=enm}}, {{term|wyd|lang=enm}}, from {{etyl|ang|en}} {{term|wid|wīd|wide, vast, broad, long; distant, far|lang=ang}}, from {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{term/t|gem-pro|*wīdaz}}, from {{etyl|ine-pro|en}} {{term/t|ine-pro|*wī-||apart, asunder, in two}}, from {{etyl|ine-pro|en}} {{term/t|ine-pro|*weye-||to drive, separate}}. Cognate with {{etyl|sco|-}} {{term|wyd|lang=sco}}, {{term|wid||of great extent; vast|lang=sco}}, {{etyl|fy|-}} {{term|wiid||broad; wide|lang=fy}}, Dutch {{term|wijd||wide; large; broad|lang=nl}}, German {{term|weit||far; wide; broad|lang=de}}, Swedish {{term|vid||wide|lang=sv}}, {{etyl|is|-}} {{term|víður||wide|lang=is}}, {{etyl|la|-}} {{term|divido|dīvidō|separate, sunder|lang=la}}, {{etyl|la|-}} {{term|vito|vītō|avoid, shun|lang=la}}. Related to {{l|en|widow}}.

